1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:26,850 --> 00:00:28,370
Good day, Vespolek.

3
00:00:32,550 --> 00:00:33,210
That's the boss.

4
00:00:36,250 --> 00:00:36,820
Oh, nice to meet you.

5
00:01:00,850 --> 00:01:04,150
Why are we even doing an ad for some pantomime festival?

6
00:01:05,050 --> 00:01:09,550
At first I wanted to throw him out, but then he kind of talked me into it.

7
00:01:43,970 --> 00:01:45,210
Sorry I'm late.

8
00:01:45,950 --> 00:01:46,870
I had a test.

9
00:01:47,150 --> 00:01:48,450
With egg yolk pastries?

10
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:49,760
Cream?

11
00:01:50,750 --> 00:01:52,480
So you were at the bakery.

12
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:53,240
It works.

13
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:53,780
What?

14
00:01:55,550 --> 00:01:57,050
Horoscopes from Astral magazine.

15
00:01:57,150 --> 00:01:59,050
Look, this is what I have for today.

16
00:01:59,240 --> 00:01:59,800
Here.

17
00:02:00,630 --> 00:02:01,190
See?

18
00:02:01,370 --> 00:02:01,930
Work.

19
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:04,870
The boss will be late but in a good mood.

20
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:07,750
So you mainly come late from the bakery across the street.

21
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:09,830
That was just a coincidence.

22
00:02:09,990 --> 00:02:10,370
No, no, no.

23
00:02:10,370 --> 00:02:13,350
It's been working since this morning, absolutely flawlessly.

24
00:02:14,150 --> 00:02:18,250
An unknown man with a medallion will cause you financial loss?

25
00:02:19,550 --> 00:02:20,760
A ticket inspector caught me this morning.

26
00:02:21,050 --> 00:02:22,450
I paid a thousand crowns.

27
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:24,610
I still don't believe it.

28
00:02:25,050 --> 00:02:26,430
But you were at the bakery.

29
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:28,810
You don't need a horoscope for that.

30
00:02:28,810 --> 00:02:30,910
I said there are parent-teacher conferences today.

31
00:02:31,270 --> 00:02:33,390
So obviously I had to calm my nerves.

32
00:02:34,350 --> 00:02:36,550
Now this is really nonsense.

33
00:02:36,650 --> 00:02:40,350
Your afternoon will be ruined by a limping man with a hoof.

34
00:02:40,950 --> 00:02:43,950
Marcelka, that sounds like some fairy tale.

35
00:02:47,650 --> 00:02:50,310
Bro, I scored a forced sale of discounted meat.

36
00:02:50,650 --> 00:02:51,650
I'm making aspic.

37
00:03:08,350 --> 00:03:10,050
He's so convincing.

38
00:03:11,950 --> 00:03:13,620
Walking against the wind, what's the point?

39
00:03:13,850 --> 00:03:15,800
Don't be such a grouch and enjoy it.

40
00:03:16,150 --> 00:03:17,060
It's free.

41
00:03:17,060 --> 00:03:18,080
That's true.

42
00:03:22,050 --> 00:03:23,850
Look, bro, not a single bristle.

43
00:03:24,450 --> 00:03:27,050
I told you it won't stink in here.

44
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:28,440
I'll take it to the yard then.

45
00:03:28,940 --> 00:03:29,420
Nowhere.

46
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,820
Not until after work.

47
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:34,850
I'm taking my aspic day off.

48
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:38,550
What kind of nonsense is that?

49
00:03:38,550 --> 00:03:39,390
What nonsense?

50
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:40,190
It's in my contract.

51
00:03:40,390 --> 00:03:41,130
Paragraph two.

52
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:47,650
You're letting him leave with such a dumb excuse?

53
00:03:48,950 --> 00:03:52,790
Well, to be honest, Ozzak really does have aspic days in his contract.

54
00:03:52,790 --> 00:03:53,590
That's our fault.

55
00:03:54,550 --> 00:03:55,820
He had me against the wall.

56
00:03:56,150 --> 00:03:58,150
Either aspic days or meal vouchers.

57
00:03:58,450 --> 00:04:00,250
Ozzak wanted meal vouchers?

58
00:04:01,350 --> 00:04:02,650
You think he was bluffing?

59
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,050
Tomas, he does whatever he wants with you.

60
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:08,030
Marcelka, could you fill in for him today?

61
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:12,250
A ruined afternoon isn't what I had in mind.

62
00:04:12,780 --> 00:04:13,340
Just this once.

63
00:04:14,350 --> 00:04:15,510
Oh, fine.

64
00:04:16,050 --> 00:04:19,750
Astral says I should offer help to a lady with a big nose today.

65
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:25,050
And that I'll save my private life from disaster if I spend tonight away from home.

66
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:27,250
So you're in luck.

67
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:31,560
Won't Zoran be upset that you're leaving him home alone because of a horoscope?

68
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:37,650
He grumbled a bit, but promised he could handle the party with the Russian ballerinas at our place on his own.

69
00:04:48,850 --> 00:04:51,210
Jesus, I thought it was regular sugar.

70
00:04:51,210 --> 00:04:52,150
We only have this kind.

71
00:04:52,650 --> 00:04:54,650
Omitko, do you need any?

72
00:04:56,450 --> 00:04:57,350
I'll take it home then.

73
00:04:57,350 --> 00:04:58,210
Later.

74
00:04:58,210 --> 00:04:59,650
Help me tear it up now.

75
00:05:02,050 --> 00:05:03,900
We shouldn't put too much in.

76
00:05:04,050 --> 00:05:05,860
Just tear, otherwise I won't survive today.

77
00:05:06,250 --> 00:05:09,650
When dad finds out about the C in history, he'll need to calm his nerves.

78
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:10,900
It's not healthy.

79
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:11,420
Yeah.

80
00:05:12,050 --> 00:05:13,450
But dad can handle it.

81
00:05:14,350 --> 00:05:16,310
As long as they don't end up like Lexa and me.

82
00:05:16,310 --> 00:05:16,970
What do you mean?

83
00:05:17,450 --> 00:05:19,050
We're allergic to sweets.

84
00:05:19,250 --> 00:05:21,450
Candies or cakes could kill us.

85
00:05:21,910 --> 00:05:22,350
Really?

86
00:05:22,950 --> 00:05:23,650
Since when?

87
00:05:24,050 --> 00:05:26,250
About a month ago, the doctor told mom.

88
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:26,690
Oh.

89
00:05:27,550 --> 00:05:29,910
A month ago they opened that new bakery across the street, right?

90
00:05:29,910 --> 00:05:31,530
Yeah, that's the bad luck.

91
00:05:31,950 --> 00:05:34,550
The bad luck is that there's a parent-teacher conference today, so keep tearing.

92
00:05:35,350 --> 00:05:38,150
If this bread pudding isn't sweet as a lollipop, I'm in trouble.

93
00:05:38,550 --> 00:05:42,300
Last time I only had a C in music and he yelled at me even despite the Bundt cake with whipped cream.

94
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:43,750
Lucky you.

95
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:44,720
What?

96
00:05:45,150 --> 00:05:46,650
Your dad likes A's.

97
00:05:47,350 --> 00:05:49,350
No he doesn't, because I don't get them.

98
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:50,180
I do.

99
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:53,550
Don't worry about your mom, she's weird.

100
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:55,150
No she's not.

101
00:05:55,540 --> 00:06:00,160
Sorry, but if she really takes your lamp just so you won't study and get C's, that's weird.

102
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:04,280
Mom says the stalks of grain that stick up the highest get cut first.

103
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,380
And she doesn't take my lamp.

104
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,880
No, and what about when you won that Czech language competition?

105
00:06:08,170 --> 00:06:10,030
She took my light bulb, and only for a week.

106
00:06:13,050 --> 00:06:15,560
Sis, I sat on some chewing gum.

107
00:06:16,550 --> 00:06:18,180
Sweetheart, I don't need this now.

108
00:06:18,180 --> 00:06:19,420
In the bathroom.

109
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,200
Go wash it off then.

110
00:06:21,780 --> 00:06:22,300
Yeah.

111
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:25,750
You need to pour acid on it for me.

112
00:06:47,450 --> 00:06:48,650
He smeared our shop window.

113
00:06:49,550 --> 00:06:51,000
Imaginary glass.

114
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:52,940
He definitely didn't even touch the window.

115
00:06:52,940 --> 00:06:53,600
Let's hope so.

116
00:06:54,850 --> 00:06:56,540
We should shoo him away somehow.

117
00:06:56,850 --> 00:06:58,050
He's wearing gloves.

118
00:06:59,590 --> 00:07:00,110
Hey.

119
00:07:02,850 --> 00:07:03,790
Ozzak is making aspic?

120
00:07:03,790 --> 00:07:03,930
Yeah.

121
00:07:04,650 --> 00:07:05,990
And tonight's the parent-teacher conference?

122
00:07:05,990 --> 00:07:06,330
Yeah.

123
00:07:06,850 --> 00:07:07,650
Damn.

124
00:07:08,450 --> 00:07:09,850
Couldn't Horvat go for you?

125
00:07:10,650 --> 00:07:12,130
But what if Horvat went for me?

126
00:07:12,310 --> 00:07:13,210
Because he can't go for me.

127
00:07:13,490 --> 00:07:17,310
Simona, does Mr. Horvat go to parent-teacher conferences for you?

128
00:07:17,470 --> 00:07:18,670
Of course, I don't have the nerves for it.

129
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:25,050
Now it makes sense why you always sit in the last row with a mask over your face.

130
00:07:25,150 --> 00:07:26,720
But that's over now.

131
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,900
Horvat lost the black wig he was wearing.

132
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,120
He only has the gray one left.

133
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,620
I don't want to look old at school.

134
00:07:32,050 --> 00:07:34,050
That shouldn't matter to you.

135
00:07:34,090 --> 00:07:36,110
Damn it, why would Horvat go to school for me?

136
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:37,750
Because I need someone to watch Ozzak.

137
00:07:38,050 --> 00:07:41,630
I'll be at school, Ozzak's making aspic and he'll be incredibly thirsty.

138
00:07:41,730 --> 00:07:43,230
Should I let him drink without supervision?

139
00:07:43,510 --> 00:07:43,970
Of course not.

140
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:44,790
See.

141
00:07:46,050 --> 00:07:48,850
Simona, if you want, I'll watch Ozzak for you.

142
00:07:49,370 --> 00:07:49,830
Really?

143
00:07:50,850 --> 00:07:52,650
Is that because of my beautiful eyes?

144
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:55,450
Not because of the eyes.

145
00:07:56,110 --> 00:07:56,790
Fine then.

146
00:07:58,950 --> 00:08:11,530
It's disgusting.

147
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:12,650
I'm making aspic.

148
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:13,710
I know.

149
00:08:14,210 --> 00:08:15,570
Well fine, it's in my contract.

150
00:08:15,610 --> 00:08:16,710
You don't have any contract with me.

151
00:08:16,810 --> 00:08:18,030
Ivuska, it's going to cool down now.

152
00:08:18,950 --> 00:08:20,650
Wait, where did you cook this?

153
00:08:20,950 --> 00:08:22,310
On the heating boiler again?

154
00:08:22,630 --> 00:08:23,930
Like I'm some kind of amateur.

155
00:08:24,550 --> 00:08:25,250
In the washing machine.

156
00:08:25,710 --> 00:08:26,990
That's absolutely possible.

157
00:08:27,150 --> 00:08:27,330
Is it?

158
00:08:27,890 --> 00:08:30,270
I set it to boil wash and then put it on spin.

159
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:32,090
The little bones will be beautiful.

160
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:35,250
Can I throw out those old rolls? No, that's a baking tray, don't.

161
00:08:35,510 --> 00:08:36,670
What am I going to make aspic with?

162
00:08:37,050 --> 00:08:38,510
Not the tray, I'm making bread pudding.

163
00:08:38,510 --> 00:08:38,930
Bread pudding?

164
00:08:39,950 --> 00:08:41,050
Did I do something wrong?

165
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:41,760
Not you.

166
00:08:42,350 --> 00:08:45,470
Except for cooking aspic in the communal washing machine.

167
00:08:45,470 --> 00:08:47,110
Oh come on, nobody will notice.

168
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:48,850
You cleaned it, right?

169
00:08:49,550 --> 00:08:50,350
Of course, with gasoline.

170
00:08:50,850 --> 00:08:51,650
Oh, great.

171
00:08:52,550 --> 00:08:53,450
Did anyone see you?

172
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:54,950
Nobody.

173
00:08:55,550 --> 00:08:56,570
Just old Roubal.

174
00:08:56,950 --> 00:08:58,250
He won't snitch.

175
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,740
Otherwise I'd tell his old lady that he goes there to smoke pot.

176
00:09:10,450 --> 00:09:12,050
I'm going to need more sugar.

177
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:25,350
She's upstairs studying.

178
00:09:25,850 --> 00:09:26,670
She's not eating anything yet.

179
00:09:27,950 --> 00:09:29,150
Just calm down.

180
00:09:29,550 --> 00:09:33,080
How am I supposed to be calm when the oven was warm and the whole place smelled of cinnamon?

181
00:09:33,450 --> 00:09:37,220
With the best will in the world, there's nothing scary about what she's doing today.

182
00:09:37,350 --> 00:09:40,450
You think Iva would bake if she hadn't done anything wrong?

183
00:09:40,450 --> 00:09:41,540
Hard to say.

184
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:41,980
She wouldn't.

185
00:09:42,380 --> 00:09:44,920
When everything's fine, I can't even get a pudding out of her.

186
00:09:45,020 --> 00:09:47,340
But when she's in trouble, she turns into a proper pastry chef.

187
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,280
Now I understand.

188
00:09:48,980 --> 00:09:50,200
She manipulates me through sweets.

189
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,520
She thinks I don't know.

190
00:09:51,940 --> 00:09:53,720
Every father has his weak spot.

191
00:09:53,780 --> 00:09:55,540
Mine was foot massages.

192
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:56,240
Right.

193
00:09:56,240 --> 00:10:02,550
And what would your father think if he went to a parent-teacher conference and saw you pouring Karlsbad salts into a basin?

194
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:05,250
That we ran out of rose petals.

195
00:10:06,650 --> 00:10:07,450
Lucky man.

196
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:09,600
I'm nervous as a dog.

197
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:11,880
And look at me, I'm calm.

198
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:16,340
Just yesterday, a man on fire in a store would have thrown me off for the entire afternoon.

199
00:10:19,450 --> 00:10:20,790
Did you say a man on fire?

200
00:10:21,050 --> 00:10:23,250
Well, that's what it said in the horoscope.

201
00:10:23,550 --> 00:10:26,750
But in reality he was just smoldering when I put him out.

202
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:28,660
What on earth did he want here?

203
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:29,660
He was looking for Ozzak.

204
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:30,790
And why?

205
00:10:31,050 --> 00:10:32,250
He said he wanted to kill him.

206
00:10:34,650 --> 00:10:37,110
Marcelka, please, I don't want to hear any more.

207
00:10:37,450 --> 00:10:40,150
Ah, here it says.

208
00:10:40,450 --> 00:10:42,950
The boss will be rather apathetic in the evening.

209
00:10:43,950 --> 00:10:45,550
And it's only the afternoon.

210
00:10:45,950 --> 00:10:47,550
See, it doesn't always work.

211
00:10:53,170 --> 00:10:53,650
Hi.

212
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:55,970
I've written everything down for you here.

213
00:10:56,450 --> 00:10:59,050
Here are the keys, here's a clothespin.

214
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:01,550
He sometimes latches on like a tick.

215
00:11:02,150 --> 00:11:03,030
Let's go then.

216
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:03,950
Wait, you want to go there like that?

217
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,600
You think it's bad?

218
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:10,450
I have the same thing in red, but I didn't want to draw too much attention.

219
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:12,700
Let's stick with this one.

220
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:13,440
Fine, let's go.

221
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:14,540
Oh no.

222
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:15,080
What?

223
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:16,920
Is it that terrible there?

224
00:11:17,350 --> 00:11:19,450
In the invitation they said there'd be some Muzika.

225
00:11:20,450 --> 00:11:21,480
Karel Muzika?

226
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:23,250
He's the vice principal.

227
00:11:23,740 --> 00:11:24,180
Him?

228
00:11:24,420 --> 00:11:25,280
And that auditorium?

229
00:11:25,340 --> 00:11:25,780
Who's that?

230
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:28,050
It's where it's held.

231
00:11:28,950 --> 00:11:30,840
Simona, I don't want to offend you.

232
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:33,280
But you should maybe take a bit more interest in your children.

233
00:11:33,340 --> 00:11:34,200
What do you mean by that?

234
00:11:34,380 --> 00:11:35,880
You don't know anything about who's at their school.

235
00:11:36,060 --> 00:11:37,340
I know everything I need to.

236
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:40,640
I doubt that, since you haven't gone to a single parent-teacher conference.

237
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:43,950
Hold on, I did go, but they wouldn't let me in.

238
00:11:44,460 --> 00:11:46,340
Wait, how is it possible they wouldn't let you in?

239
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:50,050
I don't know, the janitor grabbed me right at the entrance and said all sorts of nasty, offensive things.

240
00:11:50,250 --> 00:11:52,820
Were you by any chance wearing the same thing as today?

241
00:11:52,820 --> 00:11:53,640
No, the red one.

242
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:57,340
So, shall we go?

243
00:11:57,340 --> 00:11:57,700
Great.

244
00:12:00,250 --> 00:12:01,450
It's just around the corner.

245
00:12:01,590 --> 00:12:02,710
Look at those clunky shoes.

246
00:12:03,470 --> 00:12:04,410
I forgot my glasses.

247
00:12:06,850 --> 00:12:08,590
I forgot my driving glasses.

248
00:12:08,850 --> 00:12:10,450
You'll manage, it's just around the corner.

249
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:12,160
Hey.

250
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:16,970
Hey, are you going to the beer fair again?

251
00:12:17,190 --> 00:12:18,210
No, to school.

252
00:12:18,950 --> 00:12:19,850
What are you doing here, you have the day off.

253
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:22,890
It's a disaster, it won't set.

254
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:24,890
I put it on the balcony but it keeps running.

255
00:12:24,930 --> 00:12:25,890
And it's so windy out there.

256
00:12:26,630 --> 00:12:28,070
Oh well, I'll put it in the shed.

257
00:12:28,070 --> 00:12:30,750
You're not going to leave that disgusting thing here.

258
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:33,320
Mambo, for God's sake, otherwise it won't be done by tonight.

259
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:37,350
I refuse to share a space with a bucket of filth.

260
00:12:37,850 --> 00:12:40,750
Well then, take that back.

261
00:12:41,550 --> 00:12:42,120
Never.

262
00:12:42,350 --> 00:12:45,150
Ozzak, seriously, put it by your feet, by the stove, not here.

263
00:12:45,460 --> 00:12:47,440
You can't forbid me, it's in my contract.

264
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:47,980
Tomas.

265
00:12:48,260 --> 00:12:49,140
This time I'm not joking.

266
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:49,900
I'm not joking.

267
00:12:50,150 --> 00:12:50,950
Paragraph two.

268
00:12:52,750 --> 00:12:57,150
Ozzak, aspic is not essential for performing your job.

269
00:12:57,210 --> 00:12:57,770
It is.

270
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:01,750
Just pack up that bucket and leave.

271
00:13:02,050 --> 00:13:03,450
Out there, into that blizzard?

272
00:13:07,050 --> 00:13:09,250
That's imaginary wind, you idiot!

273
00:13:09,750 --> 00:13:11,830
Oh, so now we're going to be insulting!

274
00:13:12,050 --> 00:13:13,130
Are we going or what?

275
00:13:13,130 --> 00:13:13,310
Wait!

276
00:13:14,170 --> 00:13:14,570
Where?

277
00:13:15,850 --> 00:13:17,150
You're supposed to be in the pub.

278
00:13:17,390 --> 00:13:18,830
Today I'm in charge of you.

279
00:13:19,030 --> 00:13:19,350
What?

280
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:21,830
Is this some kind of joke?

281
00:13:21,950 --> 00:13:22,450
No.

282
00:13:23,370 --> 00:13:25,250
What kind of aspic day is this?

283
00:13:25,370 --> 00:13:26,390
My aspic won't set?

284
00:13:26,470 --> 00:13:28,210
And Mamba's going to bug me at the pub?

285
00:13:28,430 --> 00:13:29,710
Wait, yours hasn't set?

286
00:13:30,050 --> 00:13:31,870
What have I been talking about this whole time?

287
00:13:32,010 --> 00:13:36,310
Great, no aspic, no thirst, so you have the day off and you can hold on until I get back from school.

288
00:13:36,470 --> 00:13:38,170
I had a feeling someone would pull something like this.

289
00:13:38,850 --> 00:13:43,850
And since Ivuska is making bread pudding for dinner, I had a shot of booze just in case.

290
00:13:44,850 --> 00:13:45,750
Bread pudding.

291
00:13:46,950 --> 00:13:48,050
And a failing grade.

292
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:49,950
That double-crossing sneak.

293
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:52,860
Come on, let's get it over with.

294
00:13:53,050 --> 00:14:01,750
Sokolovska Street is closed too.

295
00:14:02,050 --> 00:14:03,180
What a mess.

296
00:14:03,450 --> 00:14:04,320
Are you nervous?

297
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:05,450
What do you think.

298
00:14:06,050 --> 00:14:09,050
If we'd walked, we'd have been in the classroom ten minutes ago.

299
00:14:09,950 --> 00:14:11,340
Damn festival.

300
00:14:11,650 --> 00:14:14,480
Because of their festival they've closed off half of Prague.

301
00:14:14,850 --> 00:14:17,060
Can't they walk against the wind somewhere in Brno?

302
00:14:17,350 --> 00:14:18,640
Got a shot glass?

303
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:19,120
Why?

304
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:21,150
Never mind, I'll drink straight from the bottle.

305
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:22,800
Wait, you're going to drink now?

306
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:23,920
I'm nervous too.

307
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:29,980
I'm not like Horvat, he actually liked going to school.

308
00:14:29,980 --> 00:14:32,250
He always brought something back.

309
00:14:32,550 --> 00:14:35,600
I don't even know how he signed the attendance sheet.

310
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:38,180
Wait, do you also think I'm neglecting my kids?

311
00:14:38,260 --> 00:14:39,060
Why would I think that?

312
00:14:39,180 --> 00:14:40,160
Marcela thinks so.

313
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:41,420
I don't think anything.

314
00:14:41,880 --> 00:14:42,820
What do you mean by that?

315
00:14:42,820 --> 00:14:45,780
I don't mean anything, for God's sake, I'm trying to drive.

316
00:14:45,780 --> 00:14:46,460
Then just tell me.

317
00:14:47,050 --> 00:14:48,350
Leave me alone, damn it, those mimes are invisible in the dark.

318
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:54,780
Hey, stop changing the subject, look me in the eye and say it.

319
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:56,020
What the hell am I supposed to say?

320
00:14:57,150 --> 00:14:58,450
The truth, that I'm a great mother.

321
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:04,900
What is it?

322
00:15:07,150 --> 00:15:08,750
I think we ran over a mime.

323
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:28,450
I was worried dad forgot his keys.

324
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:30,350
Can I warm up here?

325
00:15:30,850 --> 00:15:31,570
What's going on?

326
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:33,950
I was trying to study without a light bulb.

327
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:35,760
And you got frostbite from that?

328
00:15:35,760 --> 00:15:38,950
The only other light bulb is in the fridge.

329
00:15:40,850 --> 00:15:47,410
And it's about Plato, so going into Russia is so incredibly interesting that I forgot to take warming breaks.

330
00:15:47,410 --> 00:15:48,370
I'll make you some tea.

331
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:50,370
Without sugar.

332
00:15:54,150 --> 00:15:54,930
Hey, sis.

333
00:15:57,250 --> 00:16:00,250
Hey, a caramel.

334
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:05,320
That's already the fifth one and no cramps.

335
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:07,220
But it could show up later.

336
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:11,420
I went to the doctor about the chewing gum, just to have him check it out.

337
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:13,740
He said we don't have any sugar allergy.

338
00:16:13,940 --> 00:16:14,980
That's not true.

339
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:15,720
Well, yeah.

340
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:18,050
But mom said so.

341
00:16:18,980 --> 00:16:19,800
That's true.

342
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:21,660
And mom never lies.

343
00:16:22,450 --> 00:16:25,550
Maybe the doctor got it wrong then.

344
00:16:26,910 --> 00:16:27,430
You think?

345
00:16:27,430 --> 00:16:29,450
It happens all the time.

346
00:16:29,650 --> 00:16:31,150
Doctors get things wrong all the time.

347
00:16:31,150 --> 00:16:34,550
So we can have sugar.

348
00:16:35,550 --> 00:16:37,350
It looks that way.

349
00:16:38,250 --> 00:16:40,070
You can come over for bread pudding tonight.

350
00:16:40,450 --> 00:16:42,050
Or pop into the bakery.

351
00:16:42,050 --> 00:16:44,610
We can't, someone put up invisible glass across the street.

352
00:16:44,830 --> 00:16:46,110
He should have gone around.

353
00:16:46,390 --> 00:16:48,270
I know, but there's a terrible wind out there.

354
00:16:48,530 --> 00:16:49,490
That's a shame.

355
00:16:51,650 --> 00:16:52,530
So, cocoa?

356
00:16:54,850 --> 00:17:08,050
Are you okay?

357
00:17:10,050 --> 00:17:11,850
Just that it was quite a bump.

358
00:17:16,150 --> 00:17:18,270
Things have been a bit much for him lately.

359
00:17:18,650 --> 00:17:22,450
I've got my own problems too, but I don't make scenes, do I?

360
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:24,490
I killed a mime.

361
00:17:24,490 --> 00:17:26,770
Easy, Tomas, you didn't kill anyone.

362
00:17:26,950 --> 00:17:29,750
This gentleman is driving your car and taking us to the hospital.

363
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:29,890
What?

364
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:30,970
My car?

365
00:17:31,330 --> 00:17:31,810
Ha!

366
00:17:32,390 --> 00:17:32,770
Sport!

367
00:17:35,650 --> 00:17:37,350
You're in shock and you're covered in white paint.

368
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:41,350
You never talk, do you?

369
00:17:45,650 --> 00:17:47,050
No, seriously, you still won't talk.

370
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:52,760
Damn it!

371
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:54,350
Well, Sokolovska is also closed.

372
00:17:55,860 --> 00:17:57,280
Damn festival.

373
00:17:57,320 --> 00:17:59,420
Now we'll have to drive all the way around.

374
00:18:21,710 --> 00:18:23,970
Fake seizures are in my list too.

375
00:18:25,010 --> 00:18:26,570
Wait, there's only a minute left.

376
00:18:28,450 --> 00:18:29,750
Five minutes left.

377
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:35,120
Pour one beer every fifteen minutes.

378
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:37,740
If he overdoes the start, he either wilts or goes wild.

379
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:43,300
Come on, Mambo, for God's sake, be at least a little bit human.

380
00:18:43,560 --> 00:18:44,200
Begging.

381
00:18:44,460 --> 00:18:45,660
Stop that or I won't be able to hold back!

382
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:47,140
Empty threats.

383
00:18:48,550 --> 00:18:49,200
I'm going home.

384
00:18:49,450 --> 00:18:52,620
You must not be thrown off by pretending to leave either.

385
00:18:52,620 --> 00:18:53,480
Yes, fine.

386
00:18:56,470 --> 00:18:56,950
Fine.

387
00:18:56,950 --> 00:18:57,850
Mambo, fire!

388
00:19:02,450 --> 00:19:04,250
Did Ivuska give you a mute too?

389
00:19:05,650 --> 00:19:06,340
More than one.

390
00:19:07,250 --> 00:19:11,250
And don't try anything else on me.

391
00:19:11,770 --> 00:19:14,230
Your horoscope says not to play with fire.

392
00:19:14,270 --> 00:19:16,230
It could backfire terribly.

393
00:19:16,270 --> 00:19:17,370
I don't believe in that nonsense.

394
00:19:23,050 --> 00:19:23,850
Divickova.

395
00:19:25,150 --> 00:19:26,150
Yes, Ivuska.

396
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:29,320
Apparently some Mr. Roubal was looking for you at home.

397
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:30,040
What did he want?

398
00:19:30,180 --> 00:19:30,680
What did he want?

399
00:19:32,250 --> 00:19:33,950
He was singed and wanted to kill you.

400
00:19:35,150 --> 00:19:35,950
Goodbye then.

401
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:42,260
Jesus, you should have had that recorded ages ago.

402
00:19:42,260 --> 00:19:59,470
Oh, it's you.

403
00:19:59,470 --> 00:20:01,450
Ivuska, is Ozzak here?

404
00:20:02,250 --> 00:20:03,750
He was supposed to be at the pub with you.

405
00:20:04,350 --> 00:20:05,920
He disappeared shortly after you called.

406
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:06,660
Along with the aspic.

407
00:20:07,650 --> 00:20:08,550
What a day.

408
00:20:08,850 --> 00:20:09,840
Have you seen my father?

409
00:20:10,050 --> 00:20:11,250
He went to school.

410
00:20:11,420 --> 00:20:13,180
But he should have been back ages ago.

411
00:20:13,260 --> 00:20:15,160
And the school said he never showed up.

412
00:20:15,360 --> 00:20:16,760
I saw him leave with Simona.

413
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:18,350
Well, she was probably there then.

414
00:20:18,650 --> 00:20:21,150
But it's weird, the principal said she went completely gray.

415
00:20:22,350 --> 00:20:24,350
In that case, Simona wasn't there either.

416
00:20:24,950 --> 00:20:28,150
Oh, well hopefully nothing happened to them.

417
00:20:28,550 --> 00:20:31,530
Don't worry, there's nothing like that in Tomas's horoscope.

418
00:20:31,650 --> 00:20:33,150
That's really reassuring.

419
00:20:33,950 --> 00:20:35,750
Although this part.

420
00:20:36,650 --> 00:20:40,550
A man in black will take you to a place where you'll finally find peace.

421
00:20:43,150 --> 00:20:45,450
That does sound a bit strange actually.

422
00:20:45,850 --> 00:20:47,050
But nothing could have happened.

423
00:20:47,150 --> 00:20:50,900
My horoscope says I'll get a compliment from the boss today.

424
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:52,250
And nothing yet.

425
00:20:57,020 --> 00:20:57,580
Dad?

426
00:21:00,650 --> 00:21:03,250
You have a lovely bun, Vilena.

427
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:16,520
Did they really only give him glucose at the hospital?

428
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:19,000
Yeah, they said he has low blood sugar.

429
00:21:19,550 --> 00:21:23,250
But on the way back he downed a bottle of plum brandy.

430
00:21:23,850 --> 00:21:25,250
Aren't you back a bit early?

431
00:21:25,850 --> 00:21:28,160
Ozzak finished early, so I closed up.

432
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:29,160
Did you block the drain?

433
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:29,820
No.

434
00:21:30,660 --> 00:21:31,180
Damn.

435
00:21:31,850 --> 00:21:34,940
I should have written "no unauthorized entry through the drain" on those signs for you.

436
00:21:34,940 --> 00:21:36,380
One can't think of everything.

437
00:21:36,850 --> 00:21:37,750
I'm off then.

438
00:21:38,090 --> 00:21:40,770
Did Horvat sign in for me too?

439
00:21:40,870 --> 00:21:42,710
You bet, Horvi is reliable.

440
00:21:42,730 --> 00:21:43,830
Horvi, yes.

441
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:48,620
It smells lovely in here.

442
00:21:48,950 --> 00:21:50,250
Were you baking something?

443
00:21:50,750 --> 00:21:51,660
Bread pudding.

444
00:21:51,660 --> 00:21:54,810
You're in some kind of trouble.

445
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:56,760
A C in history.

446
00:21:57,250 --> 00:22:00,250
Good thing it's nothing worse.

447
00:22:02,550 --> 00:22:08,350
I've simply decided I'll never get upset over trivial things again.

448
00:22:09,250 --> 00:22:10,650
Especially after

449
00:22:11,050 --> 00:22:14,150
I've come to appreciate the value of human life.

450
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:16,450
Good God, did someone die?

451
00:22:17,550 --> 00:22:19,850
I hit a mime.

452
00:22:20,650 --> 00:22:22,050
But he's fine.

453
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:25,820
They're resilient guys, these mimes.

454
00:22:27,050 --> 00:22:29,200
And you really won't get upset today?

455
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:29,520
No.

456
00:22:30,650 --> 00:22:32,500
I promised the doctor.

457
00:22:33,550 --> 00:22:40,550
And what would you do if I told you Ozzak blew up the laundry room and nearly burned Roubal alive?

458
00:22:41,550 --> 00:22:43,450
Do we have bread pudding?

459
00:22:44,650 --> 00:22:45,950
Sweet as a lollipop.

460
00:22:46,450 --> 00:22:47,650
Then serve me some.

461
00:22:49,450 --> 00:22:50,820
Would you like some too?

462
00:22:50,820 --> 00:22:52,140
You know what, I will.

463
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,420
I still can't go home.

464
00:22:54,260 --> 00:22:56,320
See, Marcelka, it's in the horoscope.

465
00:22:56,320 --> 00:22:56,900
No, actually.

466
00:22:56,900 --> 00:23:03,550
Zoran wrote that if I come home unexpectedly, I'd ruin the surprise he's preparing for me with those ballerinas.

467
00:23:04,340 --> 00:23:06,610
Let me add some more sugar for you.

468
00:23:06,910 --> 00:23:07,390
Thank you.

469
00:23:17,950 --> 00:23:19,350
Mom, you're here. What's going on?

470
00:23:20,950 --> 00:23:22,850
The one who's here.

471
00:23:23,950 --> 00:23:25,050
We're looking for you.

472
00:23:25,450 --> 00:23:27,650
It's half past ten and you're still not home.

473
00:23:27,850 --> 00:23:33,480
I still have to blow out the pipes for tomorrow so Ozzak doesn't squeak.

474
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:34,320
What do you want?

475
00:23:35,150 --> 00:23:36,540
We need to tell you something.

476
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:37,120
Make it quick.

477
00:23:37,850 --> 00:23:41,750
We don't have any sugar allergy.

478
00:23:42,750 --> 00:23:43,450
Says who?

479
00:23:43,740 --> 00:23:44,240
The doctor.

480
00:23:44,950 --> 00:23:47,950
Oh, so the doctor tricked us, huh?

481
00:23:48,630 --> 00:23:49,530
Now off you go.

482
00:23:50,650 --> 00:23:54,850
We were thinking, we'd really love to go to the bakery tomorrow.

483
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:55,700
Great idea.

484
00:23:57,350 --> 00:24:01,380
I'll get my whipped cream allergy test results in the morning, and if they're negative.

485
00:24:01,380 --> 00:24:01,940
Great.

486
00:24:03,750 --> 00:24:04,250
Now scoot.

487
00:24:06,450 --> 00:24:07,880
Aren't you coming home yet, mom?

488
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,080
No, I'm blowing out the pipes.

489
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:10,600
But hurry up.

490
00:24:11,490 --> 00:24:12,050
Right away.

491
00:24:29,850 --> 00:24:30,850
Stop that already.

492
00:24:34,650 --> 00:24:35,650
It's getting on my nerves.

493
00:24:57,250 --> 00:24:59,150
So once again, sorry, Mr. Roubal.

494
00:25:01,750 --> 00:25:03,850
So once again, sorry, Mr. Roubal.

495
00:25:04,450 --> 00:25:05,750
Fine, fine.

496
00:25:06,150 --> 00:25:07,230
I'm not angry.

497
00:25:07,350 --> 00:25:11,150
I was thinking my aspic day wouldn't work out this time.

498
00:25:12,150 --> 00:25:13,550
Aspic day?

499
00:25:13,750 --> 00:25:19,850
Yeah, I always get a day off from work and spend the whole day making aspic.

500
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:22,240
It's in my contract.

501
00:25:23,650 --> 00:25:24,650
This year I have six.

502
00:25:26,650 --> 00:25:28,980
Wow, that's better than meal vouchers.

503
00:25:29,450 --> 00:25:32,750
And next time it won't leak on you.
